    {
        "content": "<p>For reference, here's what works for example 6.2.6:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">factorial</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- takes `(0 + 1)! \\ge 2^0` to `(0 + 1) * 0! \\ge 2^0`</span>\n<span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">factorial</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- takes `(0 + 1) * 0! \\ge 2^0` to `(0 + 1) * 1 \\ge 2^0`</span>\n<span class=\"n\">numbers</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- takes `(0 + 1) * 1 \\ge 2^0` to goal</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">factorial</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">factorial</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- takes `(0 + 1)! \\ge 2^0` to `(0 + 1) * 1 \\ge 2^0`</span>\n<span class=\"n\">numbers</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- takes `(0 + 1) * 1 \\ge 2^0` to goal</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">calc</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">factorial</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">factorial</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≥</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">numbers</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>It's just odd that the original formulation that tried to reach the goal more slowly didn't work, and it's not really clear to me why...</p>",
